Privacy Policy
(Last Updated: October 22, 2024)
Please read this Privacy Policy carefully to understand our policies and practices regarding your Personal Data (as defined below) and how GameDotGravity will treat it.
This privacy policy (“Privacy Policy” or “Policy”) applies to our mobile application and related features and services (“App” and “Services”). This Privacy Policy explains how we, and our affiliated companies (“we”, “us” or “our”) collect, use, process, secure and/or disclose end-users’ (“user”, “you”, and “yours”) Personal Data while using the Services.
INFORMATION WE COLLECT AND HOW
While using our Services, we automatically collect or ask you to provide us with certain identifying details and information that can be used to identify you (“Personal Data”). We may also collect Personal Data from our third-party partners or service providers. The Personal Data we collect includes:
•
Basic Contact Information:
We collect some Personal Data from you when you provide it to us directly, such as through an email or online form, through the support feature embedded in our Services, or through another form of inquiry. This information may include your name, email, or phone number.
•
Device Information and Online Identifiers:
When you download and use our App and Services, we automatically collect information on your device, such as the type of device you use, operating system, application version, mobile device identifiers (such as your device ID). Further we may automatically collect your IP address (including location), cookies ID, advertising ID, etc.
•
Usage Information
We collect automatically information about your activity through the App (Usage Information), such as the date and time you used the App or a specific feature, features you have used, your in-app purchase history (if applicable), your interaction with ads, and data generated when you use our Services.
•
Location
When you download and use our Services, we automatically detect your general location, namely country and state through your IP address. If applicable, we may collect, if you grant us permission, other location information through your IP address, such as the city you are in.
•
Cookies and similar data collection technologies
We and our third-party advertising partners and their partners may use cookies and similar technologies, such as mobile “SDK”, to provide and personalize our Services and to provide targeted advertisements. If you'd like to opt-out from having personalized on your mobile device, please see the Cookies, “SDK and Similar Technologies” section below.
PURPOSES FOR USE PERSONAL DATA AND LEGAL BASIS
We may use your Personal Data for the following purposes:
•
We will process all the Personal Data we collect about you, to provide and maintain our Services, recognize you when you return to our apps. Our legal basis for processing is performance of a contract with you which you entered into with us when you download our App and accept our Terms of Use.
•
We will further process all the collected Personal Data to secure and protect our Services (including troubleshooting, data analysis, testing, support, fraud, reporting and hosting of data). Our legal basis for processing is legitimate interests for running our business, and the operation and maintenance of our services.
•
We will process all the collected Personal Data to respond to legal proceedings and other obligations or requirements under applicable law.
•
We will process your contact information to communicate with you about any contact forms, helpdesk support and to help you with any other matter you request for. Our legal basis is legitimate interests.
•
We will process your online identifiers, device data and usage data to perform analytics in order to gain insights into how our users interact with our App. We use first and third party analytical tools to understand how our users interact with our App. This helps us get insights into which parts of our App need improvement. With this information, we can give users a better experience (like making changes to our App, changing annoying features, or troubleshooting bugs and problems). Our legal basis is legitimate interests.
•
We will process your usage information and cookies data to serve personalized advertisements in our Services using third-party advertising networks. Our legal basis is legitimate interests (usage data) and consent (cookies and similar technologies data). To opt-out or withdraw your consent from receiving personalized advertisements, you may send us email request at robogamedotgravity@gmail.com.
COOKIES, SDK AND SIMILAR TECHNOLOGIES
We use cookies, SDKs, and similar technologies in our App to enable essential functions and provide additional features. The information collected through SDKs serves the following purposes:
•
Delivering and enhancing our services
•
Analyzing your interaction with the services
•
Displaying personalized advertisements
•
Evaluating the app’s functionality and performance
•
Safeguarding the services and users from fraud, misuse, and illegal activities
LINKS TO OTHER SITES
Our app may contain links to other services which are not operated by us. If you click on a third-party link, you will be directed to that third-party’s site. We strongly advise you to review the privacy policies of these third parties to understand how they collect and use your personal data. We have no control over and assume no responsibility for that content and third-party’s privacy practice.
DATA SHARING
We will not share your personal data with third parties unless we have your consent or there are legal basis for doing so. The disclose of Personal Data may be for different purposes, including: (i) storage of data; (ii) sharing the data with our service providers and partners who assist us with various tasks such as analytics, customer support, marketing, etc.; (iii) advertising partners; (iv) with our affiliated companies or in case of a corporate transactions; (v) when required by law to comply with applicable legal obligations; and (vi) to enforce our legal rights and to defense against any legal claims and liabilities. When disclosing personal data to third parties for processing, we require them to keep your information confidential and to only process it as necessary to fulfill their contractual or legal obligations.
YOUR RIGHTS
Under different data protection and privacy laws, you have certain rights regarding your Personal Data. These rights include:
•
Right to access: you have the right to request access to the Personal Data we process about you.
•
Right to rectification: you have the right to request that we correct any inaccuracies in your personal data.
•
Right to erasure: you have the right to request that we delete your personal data (please note that the deletion right is not absolute).
•
Right to restrict processing: you have the right to request us to restrict processing of your Personal Data in certain circumstances.
•
Right to data portability: you have the right to receive your personal data in a structured, commonly used format, and to transmit that data to another data controller.
•
Right to object: you have the right to object to the processing of your Personal Data in certain circumstances.
•
The right not to be subject to a decision based on automated processing (including profiling).
•
Withdrawing consent if we are processing your personal data based on your consent.
If you wish to exercise any of these rights, please contact us at robogamedotgravity@gmail.com.
DATA RETENTION
We will retain your Personal Data only for as long as is necessary for providing the Services and for the purposes set out in this Privacy Policy. Once your data is no longer needed, we will either delete or anonymize it.
CROSS-BORDER DATA TRANSFERS
Your personal data may be stored on servers both locally and abroad as needed for our operations. When we transfer your Personal Data outside of the EEA, we follow all applicable cross-border data transfer laws and implement robust security measures to protect your Personal Data.
DATA SECURITY
We protect your personal data using industry-standard security measures. Our safeguards prevent unauthorized access, accidental loss, and misuse of your information.
CHANGES TO THIS POLICY
We may update this Policy as our services, technology, or legal requirements change. We'll notify you about significant changes and you can always find the latest version of our privacy policy in the App, with the update date shown at the top of this Policy.
AGE LIMITATION
Our Services are for users 16 and older. We don't intentionally collect Personal Data from anyone under 16. If you believe we have data from someone under 16, please email us at robogamedotgravity@gmail.com and we'll remove it.
CONTACT US
For questions about your data privacy or to exercise your data rights, email us at robogamedotgravity@gmail.com.
